#: src/docs_inc.c:5711
msgid ""
"The format strings `$q` and `$Q` generate filenames that are suitable for "
"many external scrapers. They rely on correct schedule data that correctly "
"identifies episodes and genres. If your guide data incorrectly identifies "
"movies as shows then the filenames will be incorrect and show could be "
"identifies as movies or vice-versa. Any xmltv guide data should contain the "
"category \"movie\" for movies."
msgstr ""
"The 格式 strings `$q` and `$Q` generate filenames that are suitable for many "
"external scrapers. They rely on correct 计划 数据 that correctly identifies "
"episodes and genres. If your 指南 数据 incorrectly identifies movies as shows "
"then the filenames will be incorrect and 显示 could be identifies as movies or"
" vice-versa. Any xmltv 指南 数据 should contain the category \"movie\" for "
"movies."

#: src/docs_inc.c:5707
#, c-format
msgid ""
"The format strings `$t`,`$s`,`%e`,`$c` also have delimiter variants such as "
"`$ t` (space after the dollar character), `$-t`, `$_t`, `$.t`, `$,t`, `$;t`."
" In these cases, the delimiter is applied only when the substituted string "
"is not empty."
msgstr ""
"The 格式 strings `$t`,`$s`,`%e`,`$c` also have delimiter variants such as `$ "
"t` (space after the dollar character), `$-t`, `$_t`, `$.t`, `$,t`, `$;t`. In"
" these cases, the delimiter is applied only when the substituted 字符串 is not "
"empty."

