#: src/docs_inc.c:4861
msgid ""
"Whenever you read or write data to the filesystems, the information is kept "
"(cached) in memory for a while. This means that regularly-accessed files are"
" available quickly without going back to the disc; it also means that "
"there’s a disconnect when writing between the write request (from the "
"application) and the actual write itself (to the disc/storage) as changes "
"are buffered to be written in one go."
msgstr ""
"Whenever you read or write 数据 to the filesystems, the 信息 is kept (cached) in"
" memory for a while. This means that regularly-accessed 文件 are 可用 quickly "
"without going back to the disc; it also means that there’s a disconnect when"
" writing between the write request (from the application) and the actual "
"write itself (to the disc/storage) as 更改 are buffered to be written in one "
"go."

